<h2>ABOUT:</h2>
<p>BAST (Back And Synchronization Tools) is a set of tools to minimize
the effort required to create, archive, rotate, synchronize backups.</p>
<br />

<h2>TRY IT OUT:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Get yourself a copy of the code.
<li>From your command line, cd to the base BAST directory.
<li>Pick the command that suits your OS:<ul>
  <li><strong>Unix/Linux/BSD/OSX:</strong><br /><pre>./bast.sh --conf doc/examples/project1.conf</pre></li>
  <li><strong>Windows:</strong> <pre>./bast.bat --conf doc/examples/project1.conf</pre></li>
  </ul></li>
<li>You may also try --help for more help.</li>
</ul>